# HandsOff -- Lessons Learned (DO NOT repeat)

## 1. Test cases -- full coverage, correct folder, follow template

- Test case generation MUST produce exhaustive coverage: all positive, negative, edge cases, boundary conditions, and regression from cross_dependency_data.
- Save under `Cursor-Project/test_cases/Flows/<Flow_name>/` or `Objects/<Entity>/`. Use `Cursor-Project/config/Test_case_template.md` for content structure.
- After generation, VERIFY files exist on disk. If missing, write them directly. Update `test_cases/Flows/README.md` or `Objects/README.md`.

## 2. Playwright tests -- EnergoTSTestAgent only, framework, 1:1 coverage

- Spec MUST be created by **energo-ts-test agent (EnergoTSTestAgent)** with test case `.md` paths and Jira key. Do NOT write specs manually or with ad-hoc code.
- Spec MUST use EnergoTS framework (fixtures: Request, Endpoints, baseFixture). No custom inline `getToken()` or `apiRequest()`.
- **1:1 correspondence:** Every TC in `.md` files must have exactly one `test()` in the spec. If TC cannot be automated, use `test.skip('reason')`.
- Output path: `EnergoTS/tests/cursor/{JIRA_KEY}-*.spec.ts`. Verify file exists after agent runs.

## 2a. Validate before run (quality gate)

- After spec creation, invoke **playwright-test-validator** agent. Checks: syntax, 1:1 coverage, TC alignment, framework usage.
- If validation fails: re-run test-case-generator and/or energo-ts-test, re-validate. Max 3 iterations. If still failing, proceed and include issues in report.

## 3. Report -- ONLY Playwright test results

- Report at `Cursor-Project/reports/YYYY-MM-DD/{JIRA_KEY}.md` must contain ONLY Playwright results: per test name, what is verified, steps, result (Passed/Failed/Not run), failure reason.
- Do NOT include cross-deps, test case file listings, or artifacts.

## 4. Slack -- full report to Tester (DM) + #ai-report ONLY

- Use `Cursor-Project/config/Slack_report_template.md` format. Send full report to: (1) Tester DM (from `customfield_10095` only, found via `slack_search_users`), (2) #ai-report channel (`C0AK96S1D7X`). NEVER send to Assignee or anyone else.

## 5. Running tests -- setup first

- If `token.json` / `envVariables.json` missing: run `npx playwright test --project=setup` first (requires `.env`). Then run tests.
- Document how to run in the report. If local run impossible, state tests must run via GitHub/CI.

## 6. Agent questions after report

- After report sent, each participating agent contributes attributed questions. Format: `[AgentName]: <question>`. Send as follow-up to same Slack recipients.
